<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web">

  <ItemGroup>
    <ProjectReference Include="..\LpmSim.Core\LpmSim.Core.csproj" />
    <ProjectReference Include="..\LpmSim.Data\LpmSim.Data.csproj" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="ClosedXML" Version="0.104.2" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.Negotiate" Version="9.0.3" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Identity.Web" Version="4.8.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Identity.Web.UI" Version="4.8.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="MudBlazor" Version="7.15.0" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>net9.0</TargetFramework>
    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>
    <UserSecretsId>d895eeb3-6c53-45d7-99d2-1c4f7ead54ee</UserSecretsId>
    <!-- App version surfaced in the sidebar footer. Bump on each release;
         AssemblyInformationalVersion is what Assembly.GetCustomAttribute
         reads at runtime. See CHANGELOG.md at the repo root for the
         per-version release notes. -->
    <Version>1.14.102</Version>
    <AssemblyVersion>1.14.102.0</AssemblyVersion>
    <FileVersion>1.14.102.0</FileVersion>
    <InformationalVersion>1.14.102 — Build SKU Max country-link routing + per-country lock. (1) Child-country builds now read the parent's whboxitems (OMAN → UAE racks.dbo.whboxitems) via the existing LPM_CountryLink table — same mechanism EOM Calculator has used since 1.14.77, just retro-fitted onto BuildItemSkuMaxAsync. (2) New LPM_SkuMaxLock table (migration 060): row presence per Country = locked. Both the manual Build SKU Max click AND the nightly SkuMaxBuildScheduler check this table and refuse / skip locked countries. UI shows a red "Locked" badge with tooltip (LockedAt / LockedBy / Reason); Build SKU Max button is greyed while locked. UAE is seeded locked by the migration — delete the row in SSMS to unlock.</InformationalVersion>
  </PropertyGroup>

</Project>
